            <fr:number>6</fr:number>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a smooth projective variety over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D=\sum _1^n D_i]]></fr:tex> be a normal crossing divisor in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D_i]]></fr:tex> all smooth divisors, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j]]></fr:tex> be the inclusion of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U=X\setminus  D]]></fr:tex> into <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.
  For <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Q\subset [1,n]]]></fr:tex>, we set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D_q=\bigcap _{i\in  Q}D_i]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>In <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[l]]></fr:tex>-adic cohomology, we canonically have

  <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>411</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-i-6.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-i-6.1.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>6.1</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       R^q j_* \mathbb {Z}_l       = \bigoplus _{\#Q=q} \mathbb {Z}_l(-q)_{D_Q}     \tag{6.1}     ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

  and the Leray spectral sequence for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j]]></fr:tex> is of the form

  <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>412</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-i-6.2</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-i-6.2.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>6.2</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       E_2^{pq}       = \bigoplus _{\#Q=q} H^p(D_Q,\mathbb {Q}_l)\otimes \mathbb {Z}_l(-q)       \Rightarrow  H^{p+q}(U,\mathbb {Q}_l).     \tag{6.2}     ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

  <fr:em>By the Weil conjectures</fr:em> <fr:link type="local" href="W1949.xml" addr="W1949" title="Number of solutions of equations in finite fields">[W1949]</fr:link>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H^p(D_Q,\mathbb {Q}_l)]]></fr:tex> is pure of weight <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>, so that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_2^{pq}]]></fr:tex> is pure of weight <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p+2q]]></fr:tex>.
  As a quotient of a sub-object of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_2^{pq}]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_r^{pq}]]></fr:tex> is also pure of weight <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p+2q]]></fr:tex>.
  By <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-i-5" href="hodge-theory-i-5.xml" number="5" />, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d_r=0]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\geq 3]]></fr:tex>, since the weights <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p+2q]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p+2q-r+2]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_r^{pq}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_r^{p+q,q-r+1}]]></fr:tex> (respectively) are different.
  Thus <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_3^{pq}=E_\infty ^{pq}]]></fr:tex>.
  Up to renumbering, the weight filtration of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H^\bullet (U,\mathbb {Q}_l)]]></fr:tex> is the abutment of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-i-6.2" href="hodge-theory-i-6.2.xml" taxon="Equation" number="6.2" />:

  <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>413</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-i-6.3</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-i-6.3.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>6.3</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       \operatorname {Gr}_n^W(H^k(U,\mathbb {Q}_l))       = E_3^{2k-n,n-k}.     \tag{6.3}     ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
  </fr:backmatter>
